<TITLE> CAO sends dialogue invites to AL, BNP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 14 (bdnews24.com)  The Chief Adviser's Office has so far invited 19 political parties including Awami League and BNP to dialogue, a top official said Wednesday. The government sent separate invitations to the two factions of the divided BNP, Kazi Md Aminul Islam, secretary to the Chief Adviser's Office, told bdnews24.com by phone. Letters were sent to 13 parties Wednesday by special envoy: the Awami League, BNP factions, Jatiya Party, Jamaat-e-Islami, Islami Oikya Jote, LDP, Unity for Political Reform, Islami Shashantantro Andolon, BSD, Khelafat Andolon, Khelafat Majlish, PDP and Kalyan Party. Invitations were sent to Bikalpadhara Bangladesh, Workers Party of Bangladesh, Communist Party of Bangladesh, JSD (Inu), Krishak Sramik Janata League and Gano Forum Tuesday. "A schedule for dialogue will be finalised later," Aminul Islam said. Each party has been asked to send up to seven representatives to dialogue. In his address to the nation on Monday, chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Monday had said dialogue would begin on May 22. CPB general secretary Mujahidul Islam Selim, Workers Party president Rashed Khan Menon and JSD president Hasanul Haque Inu confirmed to bdnews24.com by phone that they have received invitations. "There is no specific date for talks in the letter. Names of up to seven leaders, addresses and phone numbers have been sought in the letter. It was said that a convenient date and time would be finalised later," Inu said. bdnews24.com/a
